HumanSays:: What is the difference between an engineer
column4: An engineer is someone who designs and builds things. A developer is someone who builds things. A programmer is someone who writes code.

HumanSays:: What is the difference between a computer and a computer program?
RobotSays:: A computer is a machine that can be programmed to perform a set of arithmetic or logical operations automatically. A computer program is a set of instructions that can be executed by a computer to perform a specific task.

HumanSays:: What is the difference between a computer program and an algorithm?
RobotSays:: A computer program is a set of instructions that can be executed by a computer to perform a specific task. An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure for solving a problem.

HumanSays:: What is the difference between a computer program and a computer?
RobotSays:: A computer program is a set of instructions that can be executed by a computer to perform a specific task. A computer is a machine that can be programmed to perform a set of arithmetic or logical operations automatically.
